filosophy.phrase: Geometry allows us to explore and comprehend the fundamental properties of space, revealing the underlying beauty and order in our universe..
filosophy.author: Henri Poincaré

filosophy.phrase: I can calculate the motion of heavenly bodies, but not the madness of people.
filosophy.author: Isaac Newton

filosophy.phrase: Imagination is more important than knowledge. For knowledge is limited, whereas imagination embraces the entire world.
filosophy.author: Henri Poincaré
